      <abstract>The University of Michigan Center for Human Growth and Development was established in 1964 to study the ways in which human beings grow and develop. It is an interdisciplinary department with faculty from a variety of the university's schools and colleges. The records date from 1963 to 2008 and include reports, committee files, administrative information and topical files.</abstract>
